channel.title: [PI] Why does it compile halfway?
channel.description:
Okay I'm am coding a PI server, but everytime I change something nd compile it It only compiles half of it, I also won't get no error or anything.
Example;
I'll change something in spawn-config.cfg and something in Config.java. The stuff in spawn-config will get compiled but the things i change in config.java wouldn't.
Anybody has any Ideas of the problem and how to fix it?

The so called help you wrote up is worthless and will just confuse the person later on when they finally in fact do learn Java.

The problem you’re most likely facing is that when you compile, your compiled classes are moved into a different folder most likely the name of the folder is “bin”. The best way for you not get stuck in such a problem is just to take the move up to an IDE, it will handle such a thing and you won’t have to waste time dealing with it.

item.title: [PI] Why does it compile halfway?
item.dc:creator: @The_Web_Guy The Web Guy
item.description:
@The_Web_Guy wrote:

When compiling a server, it takes all the .java files and converts them to a special type of encryption that can be read by the Java Virtual Machine. config/cfg files will not be compiled by this, generally with cfg files they are either ‘compiled’ when the server is ran, or there is no need for them to be compiled.

Read full topic
